dspace-development.title: Certain DataSpace Items in Collections cannot be deleted

comments.body:
This is triggered from the `dspace-jruby`, with the following:

```
irb(main):020:0> items.last.delete
Java::JavaSql::SQLIntegrityConstraintViolationException: ORA-02292: integrity constraint (DSPACE.COLL2ITEM_ITEM_FK) violated - child record found
```

This seems to trigger an Oracle session which persists and must be closed by a database administrator (please see https://princeton.service-now.com/service?id=ticket&table=incident&sys_id=7851b4911b0614105ffe217e6e4bcb30 for reference)
For the moment, I would strongly recommend that *no* Items be deleted using `dspace-jruby`.

pulfalight.title: Update to latest blacklight and arclight
keep search functionality for name (EAC-CPF) records
Implement collection-level badges indicating the access permissions for the resource
ASpace does not import/export our ark url's pointing from agents to records

comments.body:
Also need to investigate the best way of importing/handing to Lyrasis our current CPF files. ASpace creates agent records based on names found in the EAD. There is a lot of variety in the string values of the names as represented in the EADs that have already been merged into single identities in the CPF records. Not all of them have viaf or loc id's, so I expect ASpace to create too many duplicate identities. Will test.

A workaround may involve putting back a consolidated name string into the EAD based on matching cid (from resourceRelation in our CPF records) combined with the name string.

See also https://github.com/pulibrary/archivesspace-development/issues/29
Current urls are based on the EAD ark and the cid. The EAD ark exports from ASpace, but cid's are overwritten by aspace id's.

Links created internally by ASpace do export, e.g. 

```
 <relations>
      <resourceRelation resourceRelationType="creatorOf" xlink:href="https://aspace-dev.princeton.edu//repositories/5/resources/1464" xlink:type="simple">
        <relationEntry>Blair and Lee Family Papers</relationEntry>
      </resourceRelation>
    </relations>
```

This suggests a workaround where we put our CPF entities back into the EADs and import them as part of the EADs, which will trigger the internal ASpace link creation. Testing suggests that those links will then export as part of the CPF record.

For that to happen, we need to normalize the string values of the names across the EADs to prevent duplicate entities from being created.

comments.body: @tpendragon @jrgriffiniii I'm having difficulty translating what we see on the finding aids site and how records should be displayed in pulfalight. **It would be a helpful to have a sketch of where these component should appear.** Is this the issue that there should be a contents tab on the "Series 1: Selected Correspondence" and the "Acheson, Dean, 1944-1958" pages with links to their children. That isn't the case right now. Only the parent "John Foster Dulles Papers" page has the "components" tab where you can navigate all the way down. Although when you click "1921/1921" (the normalized title), the parent-child tree is rendered strangely: Overall, the default display here is quite confusing.
